WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:04.992
Dear young people, dear believers, here
we are on the third Thursday as we reflect

00:00:04.992 --> 00:00:08.381
on the cycle of lectures about love,
about relationships, about marriage,

00:00:08.381 --> 00:00:10.230
and about partnerships, and so on.

00:00:10.230 --> 00:00:14.853
I do not know whether you have watched
this, and whether you often go to

00:00:14.853 --> 00:00:18.859
restaurants, or not, but you have
surely been, at least now and then.

00:00:18.859 --> 00:00:23.173
When you go to a restaurant for dinner
or lunch, there are literally two

00:00:23.173 --> 00:00:27.487
kinds of people: those who immediately
know what they want to eat, just as

00:00:27.487 --> 00:00:32.726
we Bosnians do, and who will speak up
at once if they have it; if not, then

00:00:32.726 --> 00:00:34.575
something similar will have to do.

00:00:35.055 --> 00:00:39.658
So you have those people in a restaurant
who know exactly what they want to eat,

00:00:39.658 --> 00:00:43.974
and when the waiter comes over, if that
isn’t quite it, they know roughly what

00:00:43.974 --> 00:00:47.715
they want, they order promptly, and
they wait for their meal to arrive.

00:00:47.715 --> 00:00:51.743
And then you have the other, larger
group of people who simply do not

00:00:51.743 --> 00:00:54.045
know what they want to eat at all.

00:00:54.045 --> 00:00:57.210
Then they start pestering the waiter
with questions: "what's this?", "how

00:00:57.210 --> 00:01:01.525
is this?", "is it like this or that?",
and sometimes even go to the extent

00:01:01.525 --> 00:01:04.978
of peering at other people's tables,
and they keep asking other guests

00:01:04.978 --> 00:01:06.705
what kind of food they're eating.

00:01:07.485 --> 00:01:10.876
Primarily, you encounter that other
group of people who never really

00:01:10.876 --> 00:01:13.034
know what it is that they want.

00:01:13.034 --> 00:01:17.659
So, however much the waiter explains it
in a very kindly, patient way, they still

00:01:17.659 --> 00:01:20.126
don't know what it is that they want.

00:01:20.126 --> 00:01:24.750
You see, the most important thing in love,
in a relationship, when you are preparing

00:01:24.750 --> 00:01:28.758
yourself, and especially for marriage,
is that you truly know what you want.

00:01:28.758 --> 00:01:34.000
If you happen to get the order of food
wrong, if you happen to pick the wrong

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.316
film at the cinema, if you happen
to mess up the coffee, or something

00:01:38.316 --> 00:01:40.475
sweet, it's not a problem at all.

00:01:40.475 --> 00:01:42.714
It won't spoil your life that much.

00:01:42.714 --> 00:01:47.192
But if you don't know what you want
from a relationship or from marriage,

00:01:47.192 --> 00:01:51.030
that can seriously complicate your
life in ways you might not expect.

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.549
Sometimes people go into relationships
or unions because of a powerful

00:01:54.549 --> 00:01:58.387
chemistry between them, and they allow
themselves to fall into the relationship

00:01:58.387 --> 00:02:02.226
simply because they have noticed
that the other person wants it, and

00:02:02.226 --> 00:02:04.785
they feel good about it at the time.

00:02:04.785 --> 00:02:08.943
Yet some people indeed—quite a few,
as I have come to know—find themselves

00:02:08.943 --> 00:02:12.781
in some kind of relationship, perhaps
even in marriage, and still they

00:02:12.781 --> 00:02:17.260
do not know what they truly want
from it, for quite a while now.

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:21.503
Therefore, when we talk about marriage, a
relationship, or a long-term partnership,

00:02:21.503 --> 00:02:25.819
it is not something that can be
treated like simply ordering a meal.

00:02:25.819 --> 00:02:30.134
If you do not know in precise
terms what you want, it can

00:02:30.134 --> 00:02:33.454
lead to, and perhaps result in,
substantial and lasting difficulties.

00:02:33.454 --> 00:02:37.770
So the very first thing you should
consider this evening is: are you

00:02:37.770 --> 00:02:39.761
truly certain about what you want?

00:02:39.761 --> 00:02:43.745
Are you certain about, exactly,
with whom you really want to be

00:02:43.745 --> 00:02:45.405
together and share your life?

00:02:45.405 --> 00:02:49.720
Are you certain about precisely what
you are prepared to accept, and about

00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:52.044
what you are not prepared to accept?

00:02:52.044 --> 00:02:56.360
There exists a book by a female
author in which she explains this

00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:58.020
distinction very clearly and accessibly.

00:02:58.020 --> 00:03:01.902
She compares it to a traffic
light, a familiar image that

00:03:01.902 --> 00:03:03.314
serves as sound guidance.

00:03:03.314 --> 00:03:07.549
We know that traffic lights display
colours, after all, including red, amber,

00:03:07.549 --> 00:03:10.020
and green, but this is wise counsel.

00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:14.255
Consequently, if you know exactly what
you want from another person, there

00:03:14.255 --> 00:03:18.843
is a considerably lower chance that
you will end up placing yourself in

00:03:18.843 --> 00:03:19.902
awkward, uncomfortable situations.

00:03:19.902 --> 00:03:23.432
So first we acknowledge,
in this moment, that at the

00:03:23.432 --> 00:03:25.549
traffic light the signal is red.

00:03:25.549 --> 00:03:29.785
Do you truly know, inside yourself,
the criteria and attitudes that your

00:03:29.785 --> 00:03:31.550
partner would simply not accept?

00:03:32.370 --> 00:03:36.127
If something is flagged as red—meaning
it is forbidden—and if it is something

00:03:36.127 --> 00:03:39.884
that can no longer be tolerated under
any circumstance, you pull the handbrake

00:03:39.884 --> 00:03:41.329
to stop the situation immediately.

00:03:41.329 --> 00:03:45.375
So how is it that there are some
things about your partner that you

00:03:45.375 --> 00:03:49.711
simply cannot bear, and yet you still
continue to go out with them, to spend

00:03:49.711 --> 00:03:51.734
time with them, to see them socially?

00:03:51.734 --> 00:03:54.624
We keep returning to the original
question we started with.

00:03:54.624 --> 00:03:57.803
Obviously you do not know, with
complete certainty, the exact profile

00:03:57.803 --> 00:04:02.138
of a person, and you do not know
exactly what it is that you want.

00:04:02.138 --> 00:04:05.896
So when I say there are things you
simply cannot accept in another

00:04:05.896 --> 00:04:09.364
person, obviously not all of us hold
identical views on these matters.

00:04:09.364 --> 00:04:12.832
Some people simply cannot get past
that issue, even when there is

00:04:12.832 --> 00:04:16.300
chemistry between you, even when
you like that person very much; you

00:04:16.300 --> 00:04:19.480
cannot accept, for instance, that
your partner is addicted to something.

00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:22.944
You cannot accept that
he is not a believer.

00:04:22.944 --> 00:04:24.641
And so on, and so forth.

00:04:24.641 --> 00:04:28.317
Do you, Sunce, know precisely at what
point inside you there exists something

00:04:28.317 --> 00:04:31.710
you simply cannot accept about your
believing partner if you are preparing

00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:35.386
yourselves for marriage, and you are
thinking ahead, and you know exactly what

00:04:35.386 --> 00:04:39.628
you want in the marriage you are working
toward, as you are growing up together,

00:04:39.628 --> 00:04:43.587
choosing a life you both want to build,
and considering how you would handle

00:04:43.587 --> 00:04:45.001
disagreements and differences in beliefs.

00:04:45.001 --> 00:04:46.132
Or should we rationalise.

00:04:46.132 --> 00:04:50.656
So, for you young people, it is often the
case that we rationalise under two kinds

00:04:50.656 --> 00:04:54.050
of emotion: the thrill of infatuation
and the sanctity of someone else’s.

00:04:54.370 --> 00:04:59.467
And then we begin to justify, or perhaps
rationalise, that all of this will, in

00:04:59.467 --> 00:05:03.206
fact, eventually change, that the person
under the overwhelming influence of

00:05:03.206 --> 00:05:05.245
your powerful love will change, indeed.

00:05:05.245 --> 00:05:08.304
That is the greatest, most
staggering lie of all.

00:05:08.304 --> 00:05:11.702
You know, from psychology, that
there exist four very different

00:05:11.702 --> 00:05:15.441
kinds of character, and that a
character does not truly change.

00:05:15.441 --> 00:05:19.179
And indeed, character can be
influenced only to a limited extent.

00:05:19.179 --> 00:05:23.597
But when someone is like that,
and especially if you do not know

00:05:23.597 --> 00:05:28.355
what you want, then you must know
precisely what you do not want in

00:05:28.355 --> 00:05:30.395
your girlfriend or in your boyfriend.

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:35.284
At any cost, no matter what, even if your
emotions tremble and flutter inside you,

00:05:35.284 --> 00:05:39.951
and even if your ears feel warm to the
touch, and your heart leaps and races

00:05:39.951 --> 00:05:42.575
like a hare's, this will not pass, at all.

00:05:42.575 --> 00:05:46.075
Because this is what most often
happens, and later there are dramas

00:05:46.075 --> 00:05:48.117
in marriage, so I thought, I thought.

00:05:48.117 --> 00:05:49.867
No, now kindly open your eyes.

00:05:49.867 --> 00:05:52.783
Tonight, when you finally come
home, don't watch the series;

00:05:52.783 --> 00:05:54.241
write to the census, indeed.

00:05:54.241 --> 00:05:57.450
So, just as at the customs,
this will simply not pass.

00:05:57.660 --> 00:06:01.786
This enters a field of inquiry in
which there is no room for compromise

00:06:01.786 --> 00:06:05.027
or concession, a field that demands
unwavering clarity and firm principle.

00:06:05.027 --> 00:06:07.680
Secondly, it can also offer
something of value, something

00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:08.859
useful that carries meaning.

00:06:08.859 --> 00:06:13.279
I meet people; I encounter many kinds
of people, and yet no one is perfect.

00:06:13.279 --> 00:06:16.816
We all have certain flaws; we
all carry certain wounds; and in

00:06:16.816 --> 00:06:18.879
the end, no one is truly perfect.

00:06:18.879 --> 00:06:21.826
But we should still give
certain things a fair chance,

00:06:21.826 --> 00:06:23.300
a real opportunity to develop.

00:06:23.300 --> 00:06:27.131
And that is then the yellow light, a
signal that indicates cautious progress.

00:06:27.131 --> 00:06:31.257
If you have doubts or uncertainties about
your partner, and you feel uncertain about

00:06:31.257 --> 00:06:35.088
different aspects of your relationship,
perhaps in terms of how he or she

00:06:35.088 --> 00:06:38.920
behaves in certain situations, of course,
that is the place where work happens.

00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:44.546
And where there are already some
things you can become acquainted

00:06:44.546 --> 00:06:48.638
with, accept, and communicate
about, perhaps even change.

00:06:48.638 --> 00:06:56.822
So, do you know at this very moment of
some field, something that is unknown to

00:06:56.822 --> 00:07:03.472
you in your partner, or your partner’s
husband or wife, something you would

00:07:03.472 --> 00:07:09.098
like to explore, study, ask about,
demand an explanation for, something

00:07:09.098 --> 00:07:15.748
that isn’t on the immediate blacklist,
something that could still pass, and of

00:07:15.748 --> 00:07:23.932
course those things when we know what
we want are the ones most of you have;

00:07:23.932 --> 00:07:31.604
and these are also some things that
fall under a green light and can pass.

00:07:32.205 --> 00:07:35.216
But exactly what do you put
beneath this green field?

00:07:35.216 --> 00:07:39.734
What exactly do you place so that it can
pass straight away with your partner?

00:07:39.734 --> 00:07:43.650
And here, despite the green field, you
commit one small but telling mistake.

00:07:43.650 --> 00:07:47.867
As I just said a moment ago, you
are not merely arranging an evening

00:07:47.867 --> 00:07:51.782
out; you are preparing for marriage
and a life of forty, fifty, sixty

00:07:51.782 --> 00:07:52.987
years together with someone.

00:07:52.987 --> 00:07:57.505
And it is very good indeed that you
know clearly what you want, and that

00:07:57.505 --> 00:07:59.312
your partner knows what you want.

00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:04.734
Let it all stay a little shallow for the
moment, so when he says what is it that

00:08:04.734 --> 00:08:08.649
passes immediately with you, coming from
your partner, and then the emphasis begins

00:08:08.649 --> 00:08:13.469
to grow—on beauty, on eyes, on a haircut,
on this, on that figure, on voice, on

00:08:13.469 --> 00:08:17.987
eyebrows, on lips, and the manner in which
you carry yourself, to every glance and

00:08:17.987 --> 00:08:22.505
gesture, and the expression you show as
you listen and respond in that moment now.

00:08:23.724 --> 00:08:26.868
Well, you can clearly see
exactly what this whole green

00:08:26.868 --> 00:08:28.440
thing ultimately comes down to.

00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:31.584
It all boils down to aesthetics—the
outward appearance and the

00:08:31.584 --> 00:08:32.527
overall stylistic surface.

00:08:32.527 --> 00:08:36.928
Of course that's the first thing, but
you mustn't put that in this context.

00:08:36.928 --> 00:08:39.443
That is part of what passes these days.

00:08:39.443 --> 00:08:42.901
Wouldn't it be nicer to say
about my partner, or partners?

00:08:42.901 --> 00:08:47.302
I do like my partner; see, I
watch him and I notice how he

00:08:47.302 --> 00:08:48.560
behaves toward children today.

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:53.609
So he knows how to play with children,
and he does so with patience and joy.

00:08:53.609 --> 00:08:58.658
I see in my partner; I watch him; he
serves others, and that shows he is

00:08:58.658 --> 00:08:59.920
helpful, reliable, and considerate.

00:08:59.920 --> 00:09:03.707
I see my girlfriend stressing her
faith; she goes to church often.

00:09:03.707 --> 00:09:07.178
That means you must place other
priorities first—those that suit you,

00:09:07.178 --> 00:09:11.596
those that open wide the doors to your
heart, and then the physical appearance,

00:09:11.596 --> 00:09:13.174
the description of that person.

00:09:13.174 --> 00:09:16.329
Describe the person physically,
but you know nothing about her.

00:09:16.329 --> 00:09:20.679
You don't know at all about your family's
origins or how to properly behave

00:09:20.679 --> 00:09:22.542
toward your parents in day-to-day life.

00:09:22.542 --> 00:09:26.581
My dear, you'll truly get to know
your partners best by how they

00:09:26.581 --> 00:09:29.998
talk about their parents today,
and what that reveals about them.

00:09:29.998 --> 00:09:34.968
And visit their home to see who does the
dishes, whether your partner is the one

00:09:34.968 --> 00:09:37.143
washing up or looking after their nails.

00:09:37.143 --> 00:09:41.492
So these are truly great moments
when you can learn a lot more about

00:09:41.492 --> 00:09:45.220
what can give you the green light
for a good, lasting relationship.

00:09:45.740 --> 00:09:50.423
The aim here is not to study a
physical trip, but rather to examine,

00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:54.771
in depth, what makes your love endure
and stay strong for a lifetime.

00:09:54.771 --> 00:09:59.789
I have just mentioned, indeed, a character
a moment ago, perhaps in passing, as well.

00:09:59.789 --> 00:10:04.138
And of course we have a psychological
character within us, yet we also

00:10:04.138 --> 00:10:08.152
recognize that there is a single common
problem present in your relationships.

00:10:08.152 --> 00:10:11.832
That is, it concerns the emotional
temperament we truly discuss here.

00:10:11.832 --> 00:10:15.846
Have you perhaps given any serious,
careful thought to that at all?

00:10:15.846 --> 00:10:20.195
I frequently meet people in pastoral
care and hear, time and again, that

00:10:20.195 --> 00:10:23.875
many partners, especially those who
are married, are dealing with this.

00:10:24.425 --> 00:10:29.432
If, in their view, his or her partner
is an emotionally unavailable person.

00:10:29.432 --> 00:10:34.054
That is to say, when you read the
literature on emotionally unavailable

00:10:34.054 --> 00:10:37.905
people, psychology typically describes
either that they have already endured

00:10:37.905 --> 00:10:42.527
some pain or trauma, or that they
are presently going through it,

00:10:42.527 --> 00:10:44.453
as many researchers have noted.

00:10:44.453 --> 00:10:49.075
And therefore it is a defence
mechanism, which is why walls are

00:10:49.075 --> 00:10:53.312
built between people, and you become
emotionally unavailable as a defence

00:10:53.312 --> 00:10:57.548
mechanism, precisely so that you
and your heart can be shielded

00:10:57.548 --> 00:11:00.245
from being hurt by others, at all.

00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:05.304
Unfortunately many people shield
themselves in this way, and many

00:11:05.304 --> 00:11:10.275
have problems in relationships,
because I recall a young couple who

00:11:10.275 --> 00:11:13.438
do not live in the same country.

00:11:13.438 --> 00:11:19.313
They are in a relationship; they see
each other physically sometimes, but they

00:11:19.313 --> 00:11:21.572
are often communicating by telephone.

00:11:21.572 --> 00:11:27.447
And that girl says, every
time I end a call, I come and

00:11:27.447 --> 00:11:30.159
cry immediately and I end it.

00:11:30.159 --> 00:11:31.062
And why?

00:11:31.062 --> 00:11:36.033
Because during that call she opens
up emotionally, reveals her true

00:11:36.033 --> 00:11:41.005
self, reveals her feelings, while
in return she receives only silence.

00:11:42.385 --> 00:11:46.569
Or would you spend your entire life
with someone who is emotionally

00:11:46.569 --> 00:11:50.405
unavailable to you, a person who
cannot meet your emotional needs?

00:11:50.405 --> 00:11:54.590
So you end up talking to a
brick wall day after day.

00:11:54.590 --> 00:11:58.774
There is no feedback, no reciprocation,
because you might presently be with

00:11:58.774 --> 00:12:02.610
an emotionally unavailable person
who has to work on solving their

00:12:02.610 --> 00:12:04.354
own problem first for themselves.

00:12:04.354 --> 00:12:08.887
And that is one of those kinds of
temperaments that people sometimes accept.

00:12:08.887 --> 00:12:12.375
But perhaps you think that
this is the absolute worst.

00:12:12.435 --> 00:12:16.068
Umm, no, there’s always something
worse out there somewhere.

00:12:16.068 --> 00:12:19.298
You have these, these sunshines
of mine—emotional, dependent

00:12:19.298 --> 00:12:21.720
people who often cling to others.

00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:27.373
These are the people whom someone hurt
in the past, whom someone abandoned at

00:12:27.373 --> 00:12:29.795
some point, whom someone left behind.

00:12:29.795 --> 00:12:34.236
And such people, with every breakup,
with every departure, experience it

00:12:34.236 --> 00:12:39.485
so traumatically, so intensely, that
they suffer in a way that makes them

00:12:39.485 --> 00:12:44.330
grow even more emotionally dependent
on just about anyone they meet, and

00:12:44.330 --> 00:12:47.560
tied to them for a long time, too.

00:12:47.560 --> 00:12:51.327
And when they enter a new relationship,
they know nothing else but to

00:12:51.327 --> 00:12:54.804
love with all their hearts and
with every fibre of their being.

00:12:54.804 --> 00:12:56.253
And what do they do?

00:12:56.253 --> 00:12:59.730
They think that if they give
more, ask less, and love more

00:12:59.730 --> 00:13:02.918
every day, with patience and hope,
they will save the relationship.

00:13:02.918 --> 00:13:06.685
So, since no one returns their love
to such people, they will sacrifice

00:13:06.685 --> 00:13:09.873
themselves to a great extent,
bathe in love, pouring out their

00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:11.611
feelings, hoping this will be enough.

00:13:11.611 --> 00:13:15.089
They cannot admit a breakup; they
cannot accept that someone else might

00:13:15.089 --> 00:13:17.117
not want to be with them anymore.

00:13:17.117 --> 00:13:20.885
They cling to the idea that love
alone can fix everything, truly now.

00:13:21.125 --> 00:13:24.886
They will do anything at all, throw
themselves wholly and completely

00:13:24.886 --> 00:13:28.990
into that relationship so that they
do not have to receive anything

00:13:28.990 --> 00:13:30.700
in return—just to have you.

00:13:30.700 --> 00:13:34.462
And now look, there are two groups:
emotionally unavailable people, and

00:13:34.462 --> 00:13:38.907
those who throw themselves at love,
and do not expect anything in return.

00:13:38.907 --> 00:13:42.669
Where are we in that story,
exactly, at this moment now?

00:13:42.669 --> 00:13:46.431
Perhaps here in this context,
there are really some who are

00:13:46.431 --> 00:13:50.193
emotionally unavailable, and perhaps
there are those who do not expect

00:13:50.193 --> 00:13:52.244
love from others; they will love.

00:13:52.244 --> 00:13:55.764
They will do more, and they will
do better; they ask for absolutely

00:13:55.764 --> 00:13:57.659
nothing in return, but they will kiss.

00:13:57.659 --> 00:14:01.178
Most of the time we find ourselves
in the middle and stay there.

00:14:01.178 --> 00:14:02.532
That is not a problem.

00:14:02.532 --> 00:14:05.780
Most often we have both sides
with us, side by side, ready

00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:07.405
to balance things as they come.

00:14:07.405 --> 00:14:11.194
So please take a moment to think
about which type you fall into today.

00:14:14.765 --> 00:14:18.971
When the shortcomings of other people
distract us and pull our attention

00:14:18.971 --> 00:14:23.178
away from what truly matters, we find
ourselves facing one fundamental problem.

00:14:23.178 --> 00:14:28.086
We have no time or energy left to
properly deal with our own faults.

00:14:28.086 --> 00:14:33.344
We ourselves often carry faults of
our own, yet if we, as we so often

00:14:33.344 --> 00:14:37.200
hear in confessions and in everyday
conversations, direct all our focus

00:14:37.200 --> 00:14:42.459
solely to the faults of our partner,
husband or wife, and fail to see any

00:14:42.459 --> 00:14:46.666
fault in ourselves, then neither the
relationship, nor the bond we share,

00:14:46.666 --> 00:14:49.120
nor the marriage itself can be saved.

00:14:49.360 --> 00:14:53.860
Every proper and lasting repair of any
relationship begins with the awareness

00:14:53.860 --> 00:14:59.110
of my own self and with the patient,
ongoing work of resolving my problems.

00:14:59.110 --> 00:15:03.235
Therefore, what matters most in
any relationship is that you are

00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:05.485
honest and sincere in your dealings.

00:15:05.485 --> 00:15:09.235
Many people are afraid to reveal
themselves, and many people

00:15:09.235 --> 00:15:11.485
are truly afraid to open up.

00:15:11.485 --> 00:15:16.360
However, if we understand all of these
blocks, and all of these emotional

00:15:16.360 --> 00:15:20.860
states, how then can one enter
into a deeper and more meaningful

00:15:20.860 --> 00:15:22.360
relationship with another person?

00:15:23.020 --> 00:15:27.581
One of the things that also tends
to happen in situations like this

00:15:27.581 --> 00:15:32.493
is that a couple who have just met
can suddenly rush headlong into a

00:15:32.493 --> 00:15:36.002
deep level of feeling and intimacy,
sometimes catching them unawares.

00:15:36.002 --> 00:15:40.213
Imagine strolling beside the water’s
edge, by the sea, with someone you

00:15:40.213 --> 00:15:45.476
have only just met, and yet you
already feel the urge to dive in deep.

00:15:45.476 --> 00:15:51.090
Because you bring with you a great
deal of trust, you tend to open up too

00:15:51.090 --> 00:15:53.546
quickly, and that can lead to problems.

00:15:53.546 --> 00:15:58.459
The process of opening up and building a
real connection does not occur gradually

00:15:58.459 --> 00:16:02.670
and safely; instead, it tends to arrive
abruptly, taking you by surprise.

00:16:03.290 --> 00:16:06.564
Here's my advice to you: start
with total honesty and take things

00:16:06.564 --> 00:16:09.566
slowly, at your own comfortable
pace, one careful step after another.

00:16:09.566 --> 00:16:12.841
First, go into the shallow with your
honest self, with your expectations,

00:16:12.841 --> 00:16:15.842
and with your emotions, listening
to your inner voice and naming

00:16:15.842 --> 00:16:17.753
what you feel and what you need.

00:16:17.753 --> 00:16:21.573
Begin by connecting in the shallow, and
then, once you have already caught the

00:16:21.573 --> 00:16:24.848
rhythm of emotional connection, once
that rhythm has taken hold and grown

00:16:24.848 --> 00:16:27.849
stronger, step into still deeper and
deeper relationships, allow yourself time

00:16:27.849 --> 00:16:31.397
to observe how you respond, and how your
partner responds, and keep listening,

00:16:31.397 --> 00:16:34.944
keep learning, and keep your boundaries
clear as you grow together right now.

00:16:35.625 --> 00:16:39.661
The core problem is this: when you
have only just begun to know each

00:16:39.661 --> 00:16:43.987
other for a week, for two weeks, or
even a month, you end up spilling

00:16:43.987 --> 00:16:46.005
out every single detail all at once.

00:16:46.005 --> 00:16:46.293
Boom!

00:16:46.293 --> 00:16:50.042
You fling open the doors of your
life and reveal everything you are.

00:16:50.042 --> 00:16:52.060
And then you overwhelm the other person.

00:16:52.060 --> 00:16:55.521
Because you must have real feelings
for the person you are dating.

00:16:55.521 --> 00:16:59.269
Because it isn’t healthy if one
person starts to open up and the

00:16:59.269 --> 00:17:02.729
other... And secondly, it can
be either too much or too fast.

00:17:02.729 --> 00:17:06.190
So you need to learn to gauge
it, to pace it appropriately.

00:17:07.670 --> 00:17:12.160
Depth becomes the very place within
us where you should seek to form

00:17:12.160 --> 00:17:15.269
meaningful connections with others,
and never fall into despair.

00:17:15.269 --> 00:17:19.760
And I believe that it is everyone's
deepest longing to connect with another

00:17:19.760 --> 00:17:25.287
person in a genuine, heartfelt way, to be
seen and to belong, and that longing is

00:17:25.287 --> 00:17:30.124
what marks a good relationship, a trace
of true holiness, and not of despair.

00:17:30.124 --> 00:17:34.269
Look, I mentioned a moment ago that
there are emotionally closed people,

00:17:34.269 --> 00:17:38.760
emotionally open people, and those
who rush at us with their love in

00:17:38.760 --> 00:17:42.215
a way that can feel overwhelming,
sometimes gentle, sometimes heavy.

00:17:42.334 --> 00:17:45.728
However, where, in all honesty, can one
possibly find any middle ground, a place

00:17:45.728 --> 00:17:47.425
where such a thing would really work?

00:17:47.425 --> 00:17:49.849
When it comes to opening the
heart and practising honesty,

00:17:49.849 --> 00:17:51.303
that is, simply put: find it.

00:17:51.303 --> 00:17:54.939
I don’t know if, when you are strolling
down the street, you look at gates—every

00:17:54.939 --> 00:17:57.121
gate, the way it stands, the way it opens.

00:17:57.121 --> 00:18:00.272
For me that image has lingered since
the blessings once bestowed on houses,

00:18:00.272 --> 00:18:03.423
and I always carefully observe what
kinds of gates there are, which ones

00:18:03.423 --> 00:18:06.574
are open, which ones are easily opened,
which are operated by remote control,

00:18:06.574 --> 00:18:10.453
which are opened by a key, who must
go out to open it and cannot possibly

00:18:10.453 --> 00:18:12.149
do so unless he goes out personally.

00:18:14.429 --> 00:18:18.417
There must exist, for every context and
in every possible circumstance, such

00:18:18.417 --> 00:18:23.734
a gate, a gate of this kind, that can
always be opened and always closed, no

00:18:23.734 --> 00:18:25.727
matter what the circumstances may be.

00:18:25.727 --> 00:18:31.044
It is dangerous for us when our heart
is kept closed at all times, or kept

00:18:31.044 --> 00:18:33.370
in a state of being permanently open.

00:18:33.370 --> 00:18:38.686
Therefore our heart must possess such a
gate which, as I would say, can be opened

00:18:38.686 --> 00:18:43.338
whenever it is needed, can be opened
smoothly, readily, but in the event of

00:18:43.338 --> 00:18:45.665
danger and need can be closed again.

00:18:46.865 --> 00:18:48.785
What is it that love is not at all?

00:18:51.675 --> 00:18:56.229
Love, of course, certainly isn't easy,
and we must never lose hope, or give up.

00:18:56.229 --> 00:19:00.176
You, my sun, in love you must bravely
and patiently fight, but never,

00:19:00.176 --> 00:19:03.516
ever, fight against one another,
for love requires unity and respect.

00:19:03.516 --> 00:19:06.553
Unfortunately, it often ends
up in petty or heated disputes

00:19:06.553 --> 00:19:08.071
that test patience and loyalty.

00:19:08.071 --> 00:19:12.018
Rac, the ongoing fight, one against the
other, that never truly ends, unless

00:19:12.018 --> 00:19:13.840
both choose to listen and forgive.

00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:17.180
In love you fight, but not
one against the other; rather,

00:19:17.180 --> 00:19:18.699
one for the other, together.

00:19:18.699 --> 00:19:22.950
You must indeed fight for each other,
because no one is truly perfect now.

00:19:24.070 --> 00:19:29.918
What is allowed for all of you in
that war of love is to wage a patient,

00:19:29.918 --> 00:19:32.670
honest fight against yourselves,
against your weaknesses, against

00:19:32.670 --> 00:19:35.767
your imperfections, against your
faults, and for your relationship—your

00:19:35.767 --> 00:19:39.551
partnership, your marriage—so that
your love can shine more clearly in

00:19:39.551 --> 00:19:41.959
the light you share with one another.

00:19:41.959 --> 00:19:47.464
What I must emphasise, and what must be
understood as coming into the mix of our

00:19:47.464 --> 00:19:51.936
understanding of love, is the essential
and careful merging and balancing of the

00:19:51.936 --> 00:19:54.345
very notion of love with sexual relations.

00:19:55.185 --> 00:20:00.183
Therefore, sex is not love in any sense,
and you must keep this clearly in mind.

00:20:00.183 --> 00:20:03.932
It is the outward expression of a
certain, perhaps somewhat peculiar, form

00:20:03.932 --> 00:20:08.618
of your own love, but sex is not the
direct route or pathway toward love.

00:20:08.618 --> 00:20:10.805
You must remember this again and again.

00:20:10.805 --> 00:20:13.929
Some people think that if
they enter into such intimate

00:20:13.929 --> 00:20:15.491
relationships, then it is love.

00:20:15.491 --> 00:20:15.803
No.

00:20:15.803 --> 00:20:19.864
For that, in no way, constitutes
the direct path toward love, but is

00:20:19.864 --> 00:20:23.925
instead merely a particular means of
expressing one of the loves you bear.

00:20:23.925 --> 00:20:27.987
And one more thing that is particularly
important to remember at the end:

00:20:27.987 --> 00:20:32.048
when love does come upon you, the
story does not simply end there.

00:20:32.048 --> 00:20:34.860
Keep this distinction in mind,
always; please remember this.

00:20:35.340 --> 00:20:39.896
You are happy, you are in love; you
either love someone or someone loves

00:20:39.896 --> 00:20:44.127
you, and there, precisely the point
where it should come to a stop.

00:20:44.127 --> 00:20:48.033
You all know that that word love
is today so commercialised, so

00:20:48.033 --> 00:20:50.962
endlessly interpreted in hundreds
of ways by people everywhere.

00:20:50.962 --> 00:20:55.518
From a Christian perspective, true love is
sacrifice, the kind of giving that calls

00:20:55.518 --> 00:20:57.146
for self-denial and steady commitment.

00:20:57.146 --> 00:21:00.400
And true love must be nourished
by reciprocity, attended to

00:21:00.400 --> 00:21:02.353
with mutual care day by day.

00:21:02.353 --> 00:21:06.910
If love does not wholly transform
our lives, then it is not true love.

00:21:07.770 --> 00:21:12.049
Because, for example, is love really
love when you are the one who marries

00:21:12.049 --> 00:21:16.635
and then you have a child; the child
cries, and the partner with whom you

00:21:16.635 --> 00:21:21.220
have agreed to build a life together
rises to watch over the child, to comfort

00:21:21.220 --> 00:21:23.666
it, and you, out of love, rise too.

00:21:23.666 --> 00:21:24.583
Is that love?

00:21:24.583 --> 00:21:25.500
Yes, it is.

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:26.722
For love is sacrifice.

00:21:26.722 --> 00:21:31.002
You will not allow only your partner
to suffer with the child, to try

00:21:31.002 --> 00:21:35.588
to soothe it to sleep; you will
rise as well and stand by her side,

00:21:35.588 --> 00:21:38.645
encouraging her, and sharing the
responsibility that comes with parenting.

00:21:38.645 --> 00:21:45.764
What I mean is this: true love and a
proper relationship, and true partners,

00:21:45.764 --> 00:21:51.867
do not expect anyone to flood me with
tenderness, with constant attention,

00:21:51.867 --> 00:21:54.409
with love, and with sacrifice.

00:21:54.409 --> 00:21:59.495
Rather, true partners of true
love strive to support their

00:21:59.495 --> 00:22:01.529
partner through hard times.

00:22:01.529 --> 00:22:07.632
Remember this: true love aims to support
its partner in difficult moments.

00:22:07.632 --> 00:22:12.717
Whether it concerns a child,
concerns work, concerns a family,

00:22:12.717 --> 00:22:19.328
or concerns anything at all, when
you see that your partner is facing

00:22:19.328 --> 00:22:22.380
a challenge, you should be there.

00:22:22.995 --> 00:22:26.197
Because she feels that with you,
in sincere silence, she talks

00:22:26.197 --> 00:22:29.108
about the problem; sunshine—that
is what love is to her.

00:22:29.108 --> 00:22:32.601
For your partner cannot rest
if you are not well, and he

00:22:32.601 --> 00:22:34.348
cannot bear to see you suffer.

00:22:34.348 --> 00:22:39.588
If you do not solve the problem, it is not
only your problem, but it also comes from

00:22:39.588 --> 00:22:43.372
your partner, and he always wants to share
everything with you, without hesitation.

00:22:43.372 --> 00:22:46.283
And now I will tell you
all sorts of things.

00:22:46.283 --> 00:22:46.574
Amen.

